BHP Billiton, Miranda, SacOil May Be Active: South Africa Stock Preview

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-06-19T23:01:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-19/bhp-billiton-miranda-sacoil-may-be-active-south-africa-stock-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index declined 331.26, or 1.1
percent, to 30,669.26 at the 5 p.m. close on Friday in
Johannesburg.  BHP Billiton Plc (BIL)  : The world’s largest mining
company releases its quarterly output report. BHP shares fell
3.30 rand, or 1.3 percent, to 249.70 rand.  Miranda Mineral Holdings Ltd. (MMH)  : The minerals
explorer said it will discontinue a capital-raising plan as
talks have been terminated. Miranda’s shares fell 1 cent, or 2.2
percent, to 45 cents.  SacOil Holdings Ltd. (SCL SJ): The oil and natural gas
explorer said it is examining plans to expand in  Gabon ,
Equatorial Guinea,  Ivory Coast  and Tunisia. SacOil’s shares fell
2 cents, or 2.8 percent, to 69 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen at  at
 lvanderwesth@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
